We came to this restaurant for dinner. we heard about this restaurant from many people.  Well, it was a winning. The staff members welcomed us with a smile and we had an excellent feeling. The meal was tasty. We enjoyed every moment and we will visit this place again. Keep it up.

Great Customer Service from Management. Cashiers need a little more training. Food is hot and fresh as advertised. Additionally, you can always place a order and make the boat you want to catch . This is a great bonus for people who are pressing the clock but need a quick bite . Maybe it’s bc there is no D/T but I can say they completely exceed service times.
Only one complaint.  I got a small chili and 4 chicken nuggets.  Well that's what I paid for . Not to be a jerk but 3 nuggets is what I got.  Someone needs to go back to math class 101 ...

Very different than every wendy's that i have been! At 3 different times i have had a napkin dispute with the manager...never had that problem with any other wendy's.I commute tru there everyday ..i guessed i wont be eating there again..

I've been coming here since it has been opened. And it is still as great as when they first opened. I love their buttery buns. At first I was taken a back by greasy buns and took me a while to determine whether I want to inject more fat via buttery buns, plus FATTENING burger and cheese, but to it's own right it has won me and I only do Wendy's takeout once in a blue moon. Their healthier options and must try is their cranberry salad.
I like the 4 for 4
Overpriced. Cashier and employees have an attitude and are rude. They put bacon in my sandwich without telling me that it comes with bacon. I will never order from them again.
Wendy’s at south ferry is the greatest, excellent service. Great quality food! Stop by here and grab something to eat.
they have a good expediting system here, the 4 for $4 deal is great, I got my order in under 10 minutes but ate all my fries before making it back to work, ok bye
Worst  experience of my life, the cashier was rude and snotty. I travel back and forth from the city to Staten Island, I buy food on a regular and all i can say is how disappointed i am.

I always go for Dave's Hot 'n Juicy  - fresh American beef between nice soft buns, loaded w/ mayo. Can never go wrong!  Single, double, triple? Based on your appetite and stomach stretchability! I prefer to go all the way with triple.  Otherwise, Wendy's is Wendy's... 🍔🍔🍔🍔🍔 - 5 points!

Horrible service .. please get new people to work here . Way too ghetto

This is one of the first google reviews I have ever written because of the terrible service I received at this place! I said "hey I need to make the ferry the doors are about to close" this lady looked and me and dropped the fries back into the tray!!! I couldn't believe that she would be so spiteful and disrespectful. If your day is so bad don't come to work!
limited variety of food, but the quality is okay.

Brittany, at the register, is the best. She made sure I got my order in a timely fashion, before my boat. Even though she was ringing up customers, she made sure, updated me, and let me know when my order would be done. She is a boss. I didn't know where to leave this feed back. But her etiquette at the register is unparalleled from any other fast food experience I have had. In NY it's acceptable to ignore the' how are you' but she took her time and was so sweet. Her interpersonal skills will get her far, no matter where she wants to go. So thank you so much Brittany!!!!
